The members of the Highflyer Heroes Outreach  Ministry in Abuja recently celebrated its 7th anniversary. Speaking during a visit to the Media Trust headquarters in Abuja, the delegation, said the ministry is open to people of all faiths. The delegation was led by prophetess Happiness U. Akpan, accompanied by Elder Benedict Opara,  Johnwell Akpan and Abe Olalekan. During the visit, Prophetess Happiness Akpan stated her passion to see Nigeria move forward and how the ministry is helping to achieve that goal. “I am constantly sharing the pains that Nigeria feels as a nation which is why every morning, I make sure that I pray for peace and unity within our nation. We also do our best in helping the elderly”, she said.